    <exercise xml:id="exercise-compare-within-pain-relief">
      <statement>
      <p>
        [<em>Dataset</em>: <c>PainRelief</c>] <xref ref="augustino2023dataset"/> measured the reported pain of new mothers in Dodoma (Tanzania) at four times: near giving birth, then <m>20</m>, <m>40</m> and <m>60</m> minutes after giving birth. Mothers were administered either paracetamol or a cold pack as pain relief. Pain was recorded using a 'numeric rating scale represented by the horizontal line marked from zero to ten', where higher scores mean greater pain.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since the number of individuals is large (<m>n = 912</m>), use the summary data in Table <xref ref="tab-pain-relief-table"/> to sketch a plot of the means and the range, like that in Figure <xref ref="fig-tape-repeated"/>.
      </p>

      <table xml:id="tab-pain-relief-table">
        <title>A summary table of reported pain for mothers after giving birth.</title>
        <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium">
          <col/><col/><col/><col/><col/><col/>
          <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
            <cell></cell>
            <cell></cell>
            <cell><alert>At birth</alert></cell>
            <cell><alert>After 20 min</alert></cell>
            <cell><alert>After 40 min</alert></cell>
            <cell><alert>After 60 min</alert></cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell><alert>Paracetamol</alert></cell>
            <cell>Mean</cell><cell>7.44</cell><cell>6.89</cell><cell>4.69</cell><cell>2.84</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell><alert>(<m>n = 456</m>)</alert></cell>
            <cell>Standard deviation</cell><cell>2.01</cell><cell>1.83</cell><cell>1.49</cell><cell>1.19</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell></cell>
            <cell>Minimum</cell><cell>2.00</cell><cell>2.00</cell><cell>2.00</cell><cell>0.00</cell>
          </row>
          <row bottom="minor">
            <cell></cell>
            <cell>Maximum</cell><cell>10.00</cell><cell>10.00</cell><cell>9.00</cell><cell>7.00</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell><alert>Cold pack</alert></cell>
            <cell>Mean</cell><cell>8.63</cell><cell>5.67</cell><cell>3.19</cell><cell>0.99</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell><alert>(<m>n = 455</m>)</alert></cell>
            <cell>Standard deviation</cell><cell>1.40</cell><cell>2.03</cell><cell>1.63</cell><cell>0.99</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell></cell>
            <cell>Minimum</cell><cell>4.00</cell><cell>0.00</cell><cell>0.00</cell><cell>0.00</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell></cell>
            <cell>Maximum</cell><cell>10.00</cell><cell>9.00</cell><cell>6.00</cell><cell>4.00</cell>
          </row>
        </tabular>
      </table>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="exercise-compare-within-stress-surgery-ci">
      <statement>
      <p>
        [<em>Dataset</em>: <c>Stress</c>] The concentration of beta-endorphins in the blood is a sign of stress. One study (<xref ref="data-hand-handbook"/>, Dataset 232; <xref ref="hoaglin2011exploring"/>) measured the beta-endorphin concentration for <m>19</m> patients about to undergo surgery.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each patient had their beta-endorphin concentrations measured <m>12</m><ndash/><m>14</m> hours before surgery, and also <m>10</m> minutes before surgery. A numerical summary (from software output) is in Table <xref ref="tab-stress-table"/>.<idx><h>Software output</h><h>mean differences</h></idx>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>Explain why this study uses a within-individuals comparison.</p></li>
        <li><p>Explain why the standard deviation for the <em>increase</em> is not the difference between the two individuals time-point standard deviations.</p></li>
        <li><p>Using the data file and software, construct a histogram of the differences.</p></li>
        <li><p>Using the data file and software, construct a case-profile plot for the data.</p></li>
      </ol>

      <table xml:id="tab-stress-table">
        <title>The numerical summary for the presurgical stress data.</title>
        <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium">
          <col/><col/><col/><col/>
          <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
            <cell></cell>
            <cell><alert>Mean</alert></cell>
            <cell><alert>Std deviation</alert></cell>
            <cell><alert>Sample size</alert></cell>
          </row>
          <row><cell>12<ndash/>14 h before surgery</cell><cell>8.35</cell><cell>4.397</cell><cell>19</cell></row>
          <row bottom="minor"><cell>10 min before surgery</cell><cell>16.05</cell><cell>12.509</cell><cell>19</cell></row>
          <row><cell><em>Increase</em></cell><cell><em>7.70</em></cell><cell><em>13.519</em></cell><cell><em>19</em></cell></row>
        </tabular>
      </table>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

